instruction: Please provide an overview of the performance of value-factor indexes and MSCI USD and EUR Investment Grade Corporate Bond Indexes during the quarter.
output: The value-factor indexes across global, regional, and international markets outperformed during the quarter, with value's active return at 6.9% compared to the MSCI ACWI Index and nearly twice that at 13% compared to the MSCI USA Index. The MSCI USD and EUR Investment Grade Corporate Bond Indexes saw continued rallies, returning 1.2% and 0.3% spread returns, respectively, in excess of their duration-matched US Treasury/German bund returns. Within the corporate-bond factor indexes, carry within USD corporate bonds experienced a significant outperformance of 260 basis points compared to a relatively moderate 20 bps in EUR corporates.
